cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language processing and specifically focuses on predicate-argument structure analysis in Japanese.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper proposes new models for analyzing PAS using deep learning techniques.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the proposed models use deep bidirectional recurrent neural networks.
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is relevant as the proposed models use neural network mechanisms such as pooling and attention.
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is less likely but still possible as the paper uses deep learning techniques to analyze natural language, which can be considered a form of visual data.
